@startuml nav_context_to_speed_limit_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title NAV Context To Speed Limit Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> NAV -> ADAS -> IVI)

actor "Driver\n(Input Console)" as Driver #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nContext > Inject / Route" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "NAV\nroute context owner" as NAV #E8F7E8
participant "ADAS\nspeed-limit / zone consumer" as ADAS #FCE8FF
participant "IVI\nroute render consumer" as IVI #E8F0FE

== Route Input ==

Driver -> Panel : Set road zone / nav dir / zone dist / speed limit
activate Panel
Panel -> Panel : Write Inject::roadZone
Panel -> Panel : Write Inject::navDirection
Panel -> Panel : Write Inject::zoneDistance
Panel -> Panel : Write Inject::speedLimit
deactivate Panel

== NAV Ownership ==

activate NAV
Panel -> NAV : Inject::* route seams
NAV -> NAV : calcBaseZoneContext()
NAV -> NAV : calcEffectiveSpeedLimit()
NAV -> NAV : derive route class / guide / ETA
NAV -> ADAS : frmNavModuleStateMsg
NAV -> IVI : frmNavModuleStateMsg
NAV -> IVI : frmNavigationRouteMsg
note right of NAV
Representative outputs
- NavRouteClass
- NavGuideType
- NavSpeedLimit
- RouteAlertEta
end note
deactivate NAV

== ADAS Speed-Limit Consumption ==

activate ADAS
NAV -> ADAS : frmNavModuleStateMsg
ADAS -> ADAS : deriveBaseZoneContextFromNavState()
ADAS -> ADAS : apply gCanNavSpeedLimit
ADAS -> ADAS : speedLimitNorm / baseZoneContext
note right of ADAS
Representative outputs
- Core::speedLimitNorm
- Core::baseZoneContext
- warning selection based on speed/zone
end note
deactivate ADAS

== IVI Route Render ==

activate IVI
NAV -> IVI : frmNavModuleStateMsg
NAV -> IVI : frmNavigationRouteMsg
IVI -> IVI : deriveBaseZoneContextFromNavState()
IVI -> IVI : roadZoneColorCode / presentationMode
deactivate IVI

Driver <- Panel : Route context becomes speed-limit and route-warning state

note over Driver, IVI
Representative runtime chain
1. Input_Console injects route context
2. NAV normalizes route class and effective speed limit
3. ADAS consumes NavSpeedLimit and baseZoneContext
4. IVI consumes the same NAV state for route presentation
end note

@enduml
